text:
Bali Airport Resumes Operations After Closure Due To Volcanic Ashes
The Ngurah Rai International Airport in Bali has resumed operations earlier than expected, an official at Indonesiaâ€™s transport ministry said in Jakarta on Thursday.
Operations at the airport resumed at 14:10 p.m. Jakarta time, earlier than the scheduled 17:00 p.m. Jakarta time, J.A. Barata, a spokesman of the ministry told Xinhua via phone.
The ministry shut down operations of the airport at 11:00 a.m. Thursday due to the spread of volcanic ash from Mount Raung volcano.
